  "texts": [
    "The determination of the optimal number of nonsensical concepts to identify in our study was not specifically adjusted to specific sentences.",
    "Instead, we employed a hyper-parameter study to evaluate model performance across varying numbers of identified concepts, which enabled us to select the number of concepts based on overall performance trends.In Fig. 4a, based on the ComVE dataset, we observe a noticeable performance improvement when moving from zero nonsensical concepts (standard prompt) to one concept.",
    "The initial identification of one nonsensical concept significantly enhances both BERTScore and BLEU, as it introduces targeted implicit knowledge that helps the model focus on the key Fig. 4 Effect of identifying different numbers of nonsensical concepts on LLMs' performance using the TIP framework.",
    "In each line chart, the knowledge generator model is indicated in the title (knowledge generator).",
    "The explanation generation models are distinguished by the legend, with Llama 2 7B, Llama 2 13B and Llama 2 70B corresponding to the blue, orange and green lines, respectively (colour figure online) commonsense-violating element in the nonsensical statement."
  ]
}